    "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I can't make a real difference for my friends, then nothing I do matters and I am letting everyone down. No matter how much I try, it's never enough, so what's the point?",
    "coping_strategies": "The client tends to offer emotional and practical support to friends in distress, sometimes neglecting their own needs. They may ruminate about their friends' problems and feel guilty or inadequate if unable to help. When overwhelmed, they might withdraw or avoid social interactions to manage emotional fatigue.",
