    "rationale": "\"The close relationships with stressed friends may evoke feelings of empathy and concern, potentially leading to emotional exhaustion... The patient might also engage in self-critical thoughts if they perceive themselves as not doing enough to support their friends, potentially resulting in feelings of guilt or inadequacy... The patient may engage in behaviors aimed at supporting their friends, such as offering emotional support, visiting, or helping with practical tasks... The patient might also withdraw or avoid social interactions if they feel overwhelmed by their friends' stressors, leading to potential isolation.\""
